Patch Set 1:

> (1 comment)
**Q1)Will this feature affect OSM modules? Or is it only a use case that implies the development of artifacts like helm charts to be packaged with the VNF?**
Yes, this feature will affect OSM modules. Envisaged impacted modules are: NBI, NG-UI and osmclient. Specifically the following impacts are foreseen:

### NBI
*  Entry point to POST and GET the AI Server resources. Metadata required:
*  Name of the resource
*  Type of the resource (TensorFlow Serving, custom...)
*  Description
*  URL
*  [Optional] User/Password or Token

### NG-UI
* Graphic interface for adding, listing and deleting AI-Agent related resources.
* Basically NG-UI should support NBI updates

### osmclient
* Commands for the AI Models Server resources. E.g.:
-  ai-models-server-create
-  ai-models-server-delete
-  ai-models-server-list
-  ai-models-server-show
-  ai-models-server-update

* We will need to request credentials to connect to the registered AI-servers
* We will support LCM operation over AIAgent at the NS and VNF level. This involves adding the required operations to update the AIAgent values.yaml fields (helm wrapper)
* Add descriptor template generation and validation

Besides these 3 modules, although no updates are foreseen, the feature would make use also of:

- The LCM module, since LCM should provide all the necessary CRUD operations for the AI-Agents and the EE where the AI-Agents are deployed.
- The kafka bus, specifically for the scaling request topics.

** Q2) Will the AI agents be part of OSM? How?**
Yes. We envisage the AI-Agents functionality split into two different functional blocks: The “AI-Agents” themselves and an attached “AI Models Server”. They would be part of OSM in the following ways:
- The AI-Agent would be executed on an Execution Environment (EE) attached to a VNF or NS. Those EE would be deployed by means of Helm charts. In this regard this feature would be similar to Feature #8157 (VNF Indicator collection using Prometheus exporters, already in Rel. 8 - [https://osm.etsi.org/pad/p/feature8157](https://osm.etsi.org/pad/p/feature8157)), but deploying the AI-Agents on the EE (instead an SNMP exporter).
- AI Models Server. Although we initially envisage this as an external component (i.e., not part of OSM), in future stages it could be considered also to deploy it as part of OSM in a similar way other off-the-shelf components are deployed now (e.g., Prometheus for implementing the TSDB functionality).

**Q3) Adding AI agents per se does not make this a feature. What will the AI agents be used for?**
The most short-term use would be to trigger scaling actions on VNFs for those use cases where designing regular algorithms is not obvious (e.g., when it is not possible to define a clear cause-effect relationships - “if \<whatever\> then scale-in”). This typically happens due to the need of processing multiple metrics or data with non-obvious correlations (we consider these metrics could be both: OSM metrics and NS metrics). For these cases AI/ML can be useful, since it can be used to infer these non-obvious relationships through artificial learning. Some more specific examples could be:

- Proactive scaling (e.g., based on combined NS and VIM metrics forecasts)
- Proactive anomaly detection
- Setting dynamic thresholds (for scaling).

Also, besides the scaling actions we consider for the short-term, in a longer-term other actions could be also considered (e.g., VNF placement, healing or alerting actions); also based on the processing of multiple metrics or data with non-obvious correlations.
